    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2280709320" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2280709320" />
    <a title="J.K. Battaglia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35915670-j-k-battaglia"><img alt="J.K. Battaglia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1515972628p2/35915670.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2280709320?book_show_action=true">Jun 04, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J.K. Battaglia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J.K. Battaglia" href="/user/show/35915670-j-k-battaglia">J.K. Battaglia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/37769851-the-shadow-girl">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2280709320" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14664833118395649398"><strong>An Extremely Shy Girl Who Needs To Discover Herself</strong><br/><br/>Misty Mount has created a pleasant read about a young girl Zylia who drifts between reality and an alternate world and she doesn’t quite know exactly why. It’s a coming of age story, of sorts, where Zylia is extremely shy, unsure of herself, and feels less loved by everyone around her. And she must discover herself, her self worth, and her value to others. Misty has managed to masterfully describe a young girl’s despondency at every waking momen</span>
  <span id="freeText14664833118395649398" style="display:none"><strong>An Extremely Shy Girl Who Needs To Discover Herself</strong><br /><br />Misty Mount has created a pleasant read about a young girl Zylia who drifts between reality and an alternate world and she doesn’t quite know exactly why. It’s a coming of age story, of sorts, where Zylia is extremely shy, unsure of herself, and feels less loved by everyone around her. And she must discover herself, her self worth, and her value to others. Misty has managed to masterfully describe a young girl’s despondency at every waking moment with every possible instance of low self esteem on display. But I wish there had been more of an exploration of that alternate world in this book and not so much grounded in the real world. It was interesting and warranted more analysis, which is why I give the book 4 stars. Maybe a future book will explore that world some more.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14664833118395649398" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

